"instruction": "Load 'metric.csv'. First compute the global P95 of 'value' for each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) using the full available series (no time filtering). Then filter metric records to the incident window 2024-02-24 05:03:03 UTC through 2024-02-24 05:33:03 UTC (inclusive). For each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) that has any points in the incident window, compute: count_in_window, anomaly_count (number of points where value >= global P95), earliest_anomaly_timestamp (UTC) if anomaly_count>0, and max_value_in_window. Return a compact table of these aggregates limited to the top 20 rows sorted by anomaly_count descending then max_value_in_window descending. Also return the total number of (cmdb_id, kpi_name) groups with anomaly_count>0. Ensure global P95 is computed from the full series before filtering."
